Build-time darwinize (NO edit to the verbatim files)
----------------------------------------------------
  The vendored decoders use GNU __attribute__((alias(...))) function aliases, which
  clang/Mach-O REJECTS ("aliases are not supported on darwin"). hosted/jit68k/
  emu68_darwinize.pl (OURS) reads each verbatim file above and writes a Darwin-compatible
  COPY to build/emu68-darwin/ in which each alias declaration is rewritten into an
  equivalent plain-C tail-call forwarder (+ forward prototypes). The files in THIS
  directory are NOT modified — `diff` against upstream is empty for every one of them.
  Only the build-dir copies are compiled. This is a portability finding, not a licence
  edit: the quarantine stays byte-verbatim.

  [J5d]/[J5g] SECOND build-time transform (the disclosed [J5a]/M68k_EA.c edit) — applied to
  the BUILD-DIR COPY of M68k_EA.c ONLY, gated by emu68_darwinize.pl's `--ea-sandbox` flag
  (the [J5d]/[J5g]/apps builds pass it; the [J5c] build does NOT, so its copy is alias-only
  and links no helper). Each DIRECT load/store site whose base register holds a 68k address
      *ptr++ = ldr_offset(reg_An, *arm_reg, 0);            // (An)   modes 2/3/4 ([J5d])
      *ptr++ = ldr_offset_postindex(reg_An, *arm_reg, 4);  // (An)+  ... str/pre likewise
      *ptr++ = ldr_offset(tmp_reg, *arm_reg, 0);           // abs.l  mode 7.1 ([J5g])
  is rewritten to a call to OUR sandbox-translating emitter
      ptr = j5d_ea_mem(ptr, KIND, <base>, *arm_reg, IMM);  // j5d_ea_helpers.c (OURS)
  which adds the sandbox base (host = base_adjust + <base>, UXTW), byteswaps with REV, and
  applies the post/pre index. KIND is derived MECHANICALLY from the original encoder name
  (size/sign/index), so the patch is a pure call-substitution preserving operand order.
  abs.l (mode 7.1) is an Emu68 inconsistency — it does NOT use the funnel helpers below, it
  materialises the address in `tmp_reg` and emits a direct ldr/str, so the direct-site match
  covers `tmp_reg` as well as `reg_An`. The QUARANTINE M68k_EA.c is NOT touched — `diff`
  against upstream stays empty (verified).

  [J5g] THIRD build-time transform (the EA FUNNEL-HELPER rewrite, also --ea-sandbox-gated)
  — the (d16,An)/(d8,An,Xn)/abs.w/abs.l/(d16,PC)/(d8,PC,Xn) modes do NOT use the direct
  (An)-class sites above; the REAL Emu68 EA decoder routes them through FOUR inline funnel
  helpers (load_reg_from_addr / load_reg_from_addr_offset / store_reg_to_addr / store_reg_
  to_addr_offset). The script replaces the BODY of each (a name-based, whole-body call-
  substitution) with a tail-call to OUR j5d_ea_addr_offset / j5d_ea_addr_index (j5d_ea_
  helpers.c), which compute base+offset or base+index<<shift, add the sandbox base-adjust
  (UXTW), byteswap with REV, and do the size-correct load/store (size 0 = LEA address-
  compute, NO memory). The DECODE stays the REAL decoder; only the memory touch is
  sandboxed. Applied to the BUILD-DIR copy ONLY; the QUARANTINE M68k_EA.c stays BYTE-
  VERBATIM (`diff` vs upstream empty, verified).

  [J5l] FOURTH build-time transform (the EMIT_MOVEM sandbox rewrite) — applied to the
  BUILD-DIR COPY of M68k_LINE4.c ONLY, gated by emu68_darwinize.pl's `--movem-sandbox`
  flag (the [J5l]/apps builds pass it). EMIT_MOVEM does NOT use M68k_EA.c's
  ldr_offset(reg_An,...) sites the --ea-sandbox transform rewrites: it resolves the EA base
  ONCE (size 0, so `base` holds the 68k ADDRESS) and emits its OWN inner loop of raw, often
  PAIRED, transfers straight off `base` —
      *ptr++ = stp_preindex(base, rt1, reg, -block_size);  // -(An) predecrement save (.l)
      *ptr++ = stp(base, rt1, reg, offset);                // (An)/(d16,An) control store
      *ptr++ = strh_offset[_preindex](base, reg, ...);     // .w store
      *ptr++ = ldp_postindex(base, rt1, reg, 8);           // (An)+ postincrement restore
      *ptr++ = ldp(base, rt1, reg, offset);  ldr_offset(...); ldrsh_offset(...);  // loads
  the 1:1-MMU + big-endian-CPU assumption. The script rewrites each such MEMORY site (scoped
  to those whose base operand is the literal `base` — uniquely movem; lea/link/unlk/pea use
  dest/src/sp) to a call to OUR j5d_movem_* helpers (j5d_ea_helpers.c, OURS): host =
  base_adjust + (uint32_t)base (UXTW), a per-register REV byteswap, DECOMPOSING the 32-bit
  W-register pairs (stp/ldp) into per-register accesses, and PRESERVING the pre/post-index An
  update (stp_preindex => An-=N first; ldp_postindex => An+=N last). The non-memory base
  arithmetic Emu68 emits (the add_immed/sub_immed bumping/snapshotting the 68k An) is left
  AS-IS. The DECODE (the register-mask order — REVERSED for predecrement, normal otherwise —
  the block sizing, the base-on-the-list tmp_base_reg snapshot, the post/pre An update) stays
  100% the REAL EMIT_MOVEM. The QUARANTINE M68k_LINE4.c is NOT touched — `diff` vs upstream
  stays empty (verified). No new file is vendored ([J5g] already vendored M68k_LINE4.c).

